# Code of Conduct

We are dedicated to providing a positive and harassment-free experience for everyone, regardless of age, gender identity and expression, sexual orientation, disability, physical appearance, body size, race, ethnicity, nationality, religion, or other protected categories.

As a contributor, you agree to abide by the following code of conduct:

## Expected Behavior

- Treat all contributors with respect and kindness.
- Communicate openly and thoughtfully with others, regardless of disagreement.
- Give credit to others for their contributions.

## Unacceptable Behavior

The following behaviors are considered harassment and are unacceptable:

- Discrimination, prejudice, or bigotry in any form.
- Offensive, derogatory, or discriminatory comments, jokes, or gestures.
- Verbal or written abuse, insults, or threats.
- Inappropriate or unwelcome advances, invitations, or attention.
- Any other conduct that could reasonably be considered inappropriate in a professional or social setting.

## Reporting Guidelines

If you experience or witness any behavior that violates this code of conduct, please report it immediately by contacting the repository owner at [insert contact information]. All reports will be kept confidential and will be investigated promptly.

## Consequences of Unacceptable Behavior

Any contributor who engages in behavior that violates this code of conduct will be asked to stop. If the behavior continues, the contributor will be temporarily or permanently banned from contributing to the repository, depending on the severity of the behavior.

## Attribution

This code of conduct is adapted from the Contributor Covenant (http://contributor-covenant.org), version 1.4, available at https://www.contributor-covenant.org/version/1/4/code-of-conduct.html.
